55.4	Composition_(visual_arts)	Composition (visual arts)	In the visual arts – in particular painting, graphic design, photography and sculpture – composition is the placement or arrangement of visual elements or ingredients in a work of art or a photograph, as distinct from the subject of a work. It can also be thought of as the organization of the elements of art according to the principles of art.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2d/Jan_Vermeer_van_Delft_011.jpg/220px-Jan_Vermeer_van_Delft_011.jpg
